defaultCurrently there is a 20% ticket price premium for Ashford to London travellers on HS1 compared to a classic rail journey. In Europe, the ticket price premium is typically 70%. Recently the Secretary of State for Transport was quoted 
defaultas saying 
defaultin the context of HS2, 
default“
defaultIf you turn up at the last minute, you are going to be paying a lot of money.”
default 
defaulthttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/road-and-rail-transport/10302224/HS2-Passengers-will-have-to-pay-a-lot-of-money-unless-they-book-ahead.html
