default10. 
defaultAll of the factors listed above result in a grossly overstated amount of 
defaultbenefits. Independent bodies
default suggest a realistic be
defaultnefit cost ratio for HS2 is 0.5, i.e. 50p back for every £1 spent.
default 
defaultThat would be 
defaultunsatisfactory by Treasury rules as well as being an irresponsible use of taxpayers’ money.
