defaultDesigned in Bottleneckdefault&#xa0;
default11. 
defaultMany of the main 
defaultrail 
defaultlines serving London are close to the maximum number of train paths that they can accommodate at peak times. 
defaultUltr
defaulta high speed trains require g
defaultreater stopping distances than
default classic trains as a result of their greater kinetic energy. So an ultra high speed line can accommodate fewer trains per hour than a classic line. The UIC (International Union of Railways) has indicated that it is not safe to run more than 16 trains per h
defaultour at 350 kph. 
defaultSee Figure 2
defaulthttp://www.greengauge21.net/wp-content/uploads/Final-Report-Appendices-B-J.pdf
