defaultIn addition
default there are tentatively two trains
default 
defaultper hour to serve Heathrow. Lastly there are two more trains per hour to link with HS1 and 
defaultpresumably these go further north than Heathrow; this is in addition to the Old Oak Common service to HS1 service. So this shows that up to t
defaultwenty trains per hour are intended on a 
defaultsection of 
defaultline that can
default safely handle 
defaultonly 
default16 trains per hour. In other wo
defaultrds there is an intention to spend £50 billion on a line that has no room for expansion s
defaulte
defaultven years after it is built. 
defaultThe Victorians had considerably more foresight.
default Contractor Atkins was aware of this issue in 2008 and documented it in their report “Beca
defaultuse Transport Matters”.
