defaultDisrupdefaulttion effectsdefault&#xa0;
default20. While being ready to criticise alternatives to HS2 due to the disruption that they will supposedly cause, the DfT has not indicated how much disruption will be caused by the construction of HS2 itself.
default&#xa0;
default21. The building of HS2 will cause 
defaultvery 
defaultsevere disruption at Euston for approximately 9 years. It is likely that Euston station will be closed for some weekends and for some bank holiday periods. The number of platforms serving classic rail will be permanently reduced from 18 to 13 and the 
defaultnumber of approach tracks from 6 to 4. This will almost certainly reduce the peak time capacity o
defaultf Euston on a permanent basis (for classic trains).
defaulthttp://www.railnews
default.co.uk/news/2013/04/19-hs2-set-to-abandon-complete.html
default&#xa0;
default22. There will be severe disruption in Camden. This will affect London Overground services which carry 25,000 passengers daily. It will also affect freight operations on the most important cross L
defaultondon freight route. It will also cause traffic chaos and se
defaultriously impact Camden Market. HS2
default will also have effects on the 
defaultexisting 
defaultrail network where it joins other routes such as at north of St Pancras (HS1), Old Oak Common, north of Lichfield, Crewe, n
defaultear Wigan, Toton and Church Fenton. 
default&#xa0;
default23. 
defaultIn addition HS2’s
default construction will affect road users for an extended period with the need to cross the M1 (6
default 
defaulttimes), M42 (6 times), M56 (3 times), M6 (3 times) and M62 (2 times) as well as 47 crossings of trunk ro
defaultads.
default To bring about its construction, many large trucks will be using any roads from motorways to narrow country lanes for several years.
defaulthttp://www.cpre.org.uk/what-we-do/transport/rail/update/item/3391-striking-new-hs2-maps-launched
default&#xa0;
default24. By contrast the 51M Optimised Alternative which does meet the DfT’s forecast passenger growth requirements 
default(through an increase of standard class capac
defaultity on each train) 
defaultwould need work at just three points on the WCML. Grade separated junctions 
defaultwould need to be built 
defaultat Ledburn and Colwich, and laying of additional track to increase freight capacity between Rugby and 
defaultNuneaton. For the latter, weekend se
defaultrvices could be diverted via other rail routes while the work is undertaken. 
defaultThe 51M Optimised Alternative requires no disruption at Euston, Camden or the other places which will be affected by the construction of HS2. 
defaultTalk of 14 years of weekend working i
defaults nothing other than unfounded scaremongering. A journalist can see through that deception.
defaulthttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/r
defaultoad-and-rail-transport/10423076/Lies-at-the-heart-of-case-for-HS2.html
