default40. 
defaultI believe HS2 will not address the most pressing issue of o
defaultvercrowded commuter trains to the south and east of London. If the Government is determined to increase the capacity for users of the West Coast Main Line, then it should adopt the 51M Optimised Alternative which is far cheaper
default, can be introduced much soon
defaulter and with less disruption than HS2. There is no logical basis for spending £50 (+) billion to supplement the capacity of a line which carries 
defaultjust 
default2% of our rail passengers and does not have the standing passenger issues which ma
defaultny other lines have. How 
defaultwill HS2
default be helping the other 98% of rail travellers? HS2 is a totally ill conceived project and many people have not even studied the finer details.
default If they did, they would understand its many 
defaultfundamental 
defaultshortcomings.
